column1: # Readings for 1826 on the rainfall sheet are crossed out and marked as 'Bad'. The extremely low annual total and several zero-reading months support this. The readings have been omitted.
# South Kyme readings end in August 1869. 1869 readings after this are duplicated from Lincoln Railway Station and have been omitted.
# The grid reference provided is for the vicarage in South Kyme - the observer from 1826 was the vicar, and earlier observers were also thought to be vicars.
